--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. THE DATASET: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The transfer dataset, meaning the deal records in data.json and their
generated presentations in data.js, the deal pages, the club pages, the RSS
feed and llms.txt, is licensed under CC BY 4.0:

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

You may share and adapt it, including commercially, provided you give
appropriate credit and link back to
https://peterdsouza247.github.io/transfer-intel/

This is deliberate. The dataset is more useful to its author the more widely
it is cited, and every generated page already declares this licence in its
Schema.org markup. A restriction the machine-readable metadata contradicts
would not be worth much anyway.

Note what CC BY does and does not cover. It applies to the compilation: the
credibility scores, statuses, the evidence records and the editorial notes.
It does not and cannot grant rights in the underlying reporting, which
belongs to the outlets cited in each record. Attribution to TransferIntel is
not a substitute for their permission.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. NOT ADVICE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Credibility scores are an assessment of how well supported a published claim
is. They are not predictions, not statements of fact about any transfer, and
not betting advice.

